Attorney for Arizona Dan Knauss:  &quot;It's easy.  We don't have the money and
the resources.  I can't create that.  It has to come from Congress.&quot;

It's Knauss's office that should handle the cases now going unprosecuted.

&quot;If they close the border and shut if off we wouldn't have an issue,&quot; says
Knauss.

Lisa Fletcher: &quot;So really what's going on in the counties is a microcosm of
what is going on in your office?&quot;

US Attorney for Arizona Dan Knauss: &quot;Exactly.&quot;

Lisa Fletcher : &quot;So are you screaming to DC?&quot;

US Attorney for Arizona Dan Knauss:  &quot;They know.  We're tapped out.  We're
redlining our lawyers.  We have higher case loads than just about any US
Attorney's office in the country.&quot;

But even on top of the nation's pot pipeline, he says there's not much he
